# BPERP — Frontend patterns

## Module structure

```javascript
// frontend/js/modules/example.js
import { DOMCache, showToast, createModal } from './common.js';
import storage from './storage.js';

const state = { items: [], loading: false };

export async function init() {
    registerEventHandlers();
    await loadData();
}

export function renderView() {
    const container = DOMCache.get('mainContent');
    container.innerHTML = `...`;
}

function registerEventHandlers() {
    document.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
        if (e.target.matches('[data-action="example"]')) {
            handleAction(e);
        }
    });
}
```

## Global namespace

```javascript
window.BPERP = {
    common,      // DOM utilities, modals, toasts
    storage,     // localStorage wrapper with caching
    inventory,   // Products, parts, materials, tooling, misc
    sales,       // Customers, leads (API + offline), quotes, work orders
    tasks,       // Workflow tasks
    maintenance, // Machine profiles, maintenance tasks
    search,      // Global search
    users,       // Auth, permissions
    navigate,    // SPA routing
    config       // App configuration
};
```

## Routing (`app.js`)

- `navigate(route)` resolves `routes[route]` and updates sidebar active state.
- **`tasks-maintenance`** (**Machines**) uses `maintenance.loadMaintenanceTasks()`, not the tasks module. `navigate()` must call `modules.tasks.deactivate()` when entering **Machines** (and when leaving `tasks-*` for non-task routes) so the tasks module’s `masterTimer` refresh does not repaint `#dashboardContent` after the user has navigated away.

## Event delegation

Use `data-action` for clicks:

```html
<button data-action="delete-item" data-id="${item.id}">Delete</button>
```

## Theming

Eight themes via CSS variables in `dashboard.css`: automation (default), industrial, cyber, classic, crimson, ultraviolet, amber, midnight.
